  "text": "MG as a side-product of glycolysis consequently arises from an increased flux during hyperglycemia. MG has been postulated to play a role in the development of hypertension [CITATION_1] . Studies using animal model and cell cultures showed a significant increase in blood pressure to coincide with elevated MG level in plasma and aortic tissues [CITATION_2] . However, functional links between MG biogenesis and hypertension, in part mediated by ROS and AGEs, have only been documented in rat model but not yet in humans under these conditions.",
